===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|rood|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|rod|rōd|a rod, pole, rood (land measure), plot of land of a square rod, a cross, rood (as in Holy-rood), gallows, a cross on which a person is executed, death on a cross, crucifix|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|rōdō|lang=gem-pro}}, {{recons|rōdōn||rod, pole|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|rōt-|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|rāt-||bar, beam, stem|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Rute||rod, cane, pole|lang=de}}, {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|roda||rod|lang=no}}. Largely displaced by {{l|en|cross}}. More at {{l|en|rod}}.

